.SH EXAMPLES
\f[B]Remove comments from Go source code that has been copied to the
clipboard:\f[R]
.PP
\f[CR]nogocomments \-\-paste\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]Remove comments from a Go file and print the result to the
terminal:\f[R]
.PP
\f[CR]nogocomments \-\-file /path/to/your/file.go\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]Remove comments from a Go file and write the result to a new
file:\f[R]
.PP
\f[CR]nogocomments \-\-file /path/to/your/source.go > newfile.go\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]Enable debug mode for more detailed logs:\f[R]
.PP
\f[CR]nogocomments \-\-debug \-\-file /path/to/your/file.go\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]Print the version, build details, and license information:\f[R]
.PP
\f[CR]nogocomments \-\-version\f[R]
